@ijuma Digging in a bit further. We can't make this migration without breaking inter.broker.protocol.version for ControlledShutdownRequest. Since clientId (required by the new protocol header) was not added to the old ControlledShutdownRequest until 0.9.0 (v1). The v0 Request is not compatible with the o.a.k.c requests. We would not be able to support inter.broker.protocol.version for 0.8 versions if we make this change.

I could do the KafkaApis migration by "hacking" some special handling together in RequestChannel. But that would not remove the needed code in KafkaServer and I am not sure thats worth it.

So then the question is when can inter.broker.protocol.version break? How many versions back do we support? (I may need to open a jira to define or document that)

